FeedPackage.Description:
ver 1.1.0.50 ============================================================================= 更新了SQLBULKCOPY功能，现在可以通过SQLBULKCOPYNEXECUTE来执行批量导入同时执行相关操作的任务了
ver 1.1.0.66 ============================================================================= 增加FP/U Post接口，现在使用UApiSvc的网站可以不用自己写上传文件的页面或控制器了，FP/U可直接实现上传功能 配合plupload使用效果更佳
ver 1.1.0.90 2017-2-23 ============================================================================= 重写了ua-script内容，现在服务器端绑定可以更灵活的工作了！ ua-api内的模板HTML现在支持{{}}方式的绑定定义了，ua-attr作为一个向下兼容的选项存在，不再建议使用 pagepart组件正式启用，作为老版本sidemenu的替代品，它可以在更多的场景下工作
ver 1.1.1.12 2017-2-28 ============================================================================= 增加了ua-api的缓存功能，一次渲染过程中可以多次读取同一组数据，同时提供了dataindex指定数据集序号， 提供了prms指定固定参数，1.1.1.12大版本，开始实现不使用代码和脚本完成需求的梦想功能
ver 1.1.1.13 2017-3-8 ============================================================================= 新增mapping >OptionReplace 配置 当配置了OptionReplace="YES" Mapping 优先使用 input的内容，否则使用Mapping内容

FeedPackage.Description: Simplified syntax for sustainable automation.
FeedPackage.Title: Uber.CUIT

FeedPackage.Description: Uber.CUIT is an extension class library for Microsoft Coded UI tests that simplifies the syntax for manually writing your own Coded UI tests ( without recorder ) and provides extension methods to help you on your quest. It is ideal for use with Page Object Architecture Patterns that are commonly used in Selenium and D.R.Y. principles in order to build readable, maintainable, and scalable automation frameworks. Visit www.getUberCUIT.com for more info.

FeedPackage.Description:
Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.
FeedPackage.Tags: Signere Sign BankID Digital signatur Uni Pluss Signere.no

All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.

FeedPackage.Description: Editor for Umbraco grid that allows for easy creation of bootstrap callapsible panels / accordions. To work correctly, this plugin requires bootstrap 3 CSS/JS to be loaded into the view being rendered. For grouped accordions, please ensure the accordions you wish to be grouped have a common ancestor that can be targetted via a css selector and have the 'panel-group' class applied.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Initial version
FeedPackage.Summary: Bootstrap 3 Accordion Plugin for Umbraco Grid Editor.

FeedPackage.Description:
Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.
FeedPackage.Tags: Signere Sign BankID Digital signatur Uni Pluss Signere.no

FeedPackage.Description:
Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.

FeedPackage.Description:
Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.

Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.

FeedPackage.Description: Fast and comprehensive logging tool for .NET applications, designed for always-on logging. FieldLog allows applications to write events, data and errors (including structured exceptions with lots of details) to managed and efficient log files. The logging methods are optimised for high performance multi-threaded operation. A useful log viewer application is available from the project website.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: See changes at: https://github.com/dg9ngf/FieldLog/commits/master

FeedPackage.Description:
Fast and comprehensive logging tool for .NET applications, designed for always-on logging.
FieldLog allows applications to write events, data and errors (including structured exceptions with lots of details) to managed and efficient log files. The logging methods are optimised for high performance multi-threaded operation. A useful log viewer application is available from the project website.
Please visit the project website for further information on FieldLog, including a feature list, sample code, and a developer guide.

FeedPackage.Description:
Simple yet powerful translation and localisation library for .NET applications.
TxTranslation is a complete solution for drop-in localisation in all types of .NET applications (WPF, WinForms, ASP.NET, Service, Console). It has an easy syntax through XAML extensions and Windows Forms binding and regards a fallback language on missing translations of a text. Translation texts may contain count-specific translations and placeholders, and the library provides number and time formatting. A comfortable editor application for dictionaries with consistency checks and similar translations suggestions is available from the project website.
Please visit the project website for further information on TxTranslation, including a feature list, sample code, and a developer guide.

FeedPackage.Description:
Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.
FeedPackage.Tags: Signere Sign BankID Digital signatur Uni Pluss Signere.no
